  "prompt": "Does the government have laws against money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, governments around the world, including the United States, have laws against money laundering. These laws are designed to prevent criminals from disguising the origins of illegally obtained money, making it appear legitimate.\n\nIn the United States, the primary laws against money laundering are:\n\n*   **The Bank Secrecy Act (BSA):** Requires financial institutions to keep records and file reports on certain financial transactions.\n*   **Money Laundering Control Act:** Criminalizes money laundering activities.\n*   **USA PATRIOT Act:** Strengthened existing anti-money laundering laws in response to the September 11 attacks.",
